Search Engine using whoosh:

Code 
analyzer=ChineseAnalyzer()

class legal_schema(SchemaClass):
    title=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    content=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    court=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    category=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)

if not os.path.exists("legal_indexing"):
    os.mkdir("legal_indexing")

schema=legal_schema()

index=create_in("legal_indexing", schema, indexname='document_index')

writer = index.writer()

for index, row in df.iterrows():
    writer.add_document(content=row['content'], title=row['title'], court=row['court'])

writer.commit()

index=open_dir("legal_indexing", indexname='document_index')

searcher = index.searcher(weighting=BM25F(B=0.75, content_B=1.0, K1=1.5))

query = QueryParser("content", index.schema).parse("") # single

query = MultifieldParser(["content", "title"], index.schema).parse("") # multi

result = searcher.search(query)

result[0]. # result

result[0].score # score

library(shiny)
library(tidyverse)
library(reticulate)
library(DT)

virtualenv_create(envname = "python3_env")
virtualenv_install("python3_env", packages = c("whoosh", "jieba"))
use_virtualenv("python3_env", required = T)

whoosh <- reticulate::import("whoosh")

index <- whoosh$index$open_dir("legal_indexing", indexname = "document_index")

searcher <- index$searcher()

get_result <- possibly(
    \(x) {
        query <- whoosh$qparser$MultifieldParser(c("content", "title"), index$schema)$parse(x)

        result <- searcher$search(query)

        return(result)
    },
    otherwise = "error!"
)

ui <- fluidPage(
    tags$head(tags$link(rel = "stylesheet", type = "text/css", href = "custom.css")),
    tags$head(tags$script(src = "shiny_darkmode.js")),
    tags$style(HTML("@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora&display=swap');

                  body {
                    font-family: 'Lora', sans-serif;
                    background-color: #fdfdfd;
                  }

                    .form-control {
                      display: block;
                      height: 45px;
                      width: 100%;
                      padding: 10px 20px;
                      font-size: 18px;
                      line-height: 1.33333333;
                      color: #555;
                      background-color: #fff;
                      background-image: none;
                      border: 1px solid #ccc;
                      border-radius: 4px;
                    }

                    .btn {
                      display: inline-block;
                      padding: 10px 20px;
                      margin-bottom: 0;
                      font-size: 18px;
                      font-weight: normal;
                      line-height: 1.33333333;
                      text-align: center;
                      white-space: nowrap;
                      vertical-align: middle;
                      cursor: pointer;
                      background-image: none;
                      border: 1px solid transparent;
                      border-radius: 4px;
                    }

                    .btn-primary {
                      color: #fff;
                      background-color: #4285f4;
                      border-color: #2d7df4;
                    }

                    .btn-primary:hover {
                      color: #fff;
                      background-color: #2d7df4;
                      border-color: #1e67d3;
                    }

                    a {
                      color: #1a0dab;
                    }

                    a:hover {
                      color: #1a0dab;
                        text-decoration: underline;
                    }

                    p {
                      font-size: 14px;
                      color: #545454;
                    }")),
    fluidRow(
        column(12,
            align = "center",
            img(src = "https://www.dropbox.com/s/rpuqh8kgqcuu592/icon_revised.png?dl=0&raw=1", height = "100px", width = "200px"),
            textInput("query", "", placeholder = "Search for court judgements "),
            actionButton("search", "Search")
        )
    ),
    hr(),
    mainPanel(
        # tableOutput("results")
        DTOutput("results")
    )
)

server <- function(input, output) {
    search_results <- eventReactive(input$search, {
        result <- get_result(input$query)

        if (length(result) == 0 | is.character(result)) {
            tibble("No Result Found!")
        } else {
            return(tibble(content = map_chr(0:9, \(x) result[x]$highlights("content")), score = map_dbl(0:9, \(x) result[x]$score)))
        }
    })

    # highlight_keywords <- function(text, keyword) {
    # highlighted <- gsub(paste0("\\b(", keyword, ")\\b"), "<mark>\\1</mark>", text, ignore.case = TRUE)
    # return(highlighted)
    # }

    output$results <- renderDT(
        {
            search_results()
        },
        options = list(pageLength = 5)
    )
}

shinyApp(ui, server)

# Search Engine

Package Management
```{python}
import os
import pandas as pd
from jieba.analyse import ChineseAnalyzer
from whoosh.fields import TEXT, SchemaClass
from whoosh.index import create_in
from whoosh.qparser import QueryParser, MultifieldParser
from whoosh.index import open_dir
from whoosh.query import compound, Term
from whoosh.scoring import BM25F
```

```{python}
df=pd.read_csv("legal.csv").dropna(how="all")
```

Search Engine using [whoosh](https://whoosh.readthedocs.io/en/latest/intro.html):
```{python}
#| eval: false
analyzer=ChineseAnalyzer()

class legal_schema(SchemaClass):
    title=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    content=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    court=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)
    category=TEXT(stored=True, analyzer=analyzer)

if not os.path.exists("legal_indexing"):
    os.mkdir("legal_indexing")

schema=legal_schema()

index=create_in("legal_indexing", schema, indexname='document_index')

writer = index.writer()

for index, row in df.iterrows():
    writer.add_document(content=row['content'], title=row['title'], court=row['court'])

writer.commit()

index=open_dir("legal_indexing", indexname='document_index')

searcher = index.searcher(weighting=BM25F(B=0.75, content_B=1.0, K1=1.5))

query = QueryParser("content", index.schema).parse("") # single

query = MultifieldParser(["content", "title"], index.schema).parse("") # multi

result = searcher.search(query)

result[0]. # result

result[0].score # score
```

```{python}
library(shiny)
library(tidyverse)
library(reticulate)
library(DT)

virtualenv_create(envname = "python3_env")
virtualenv_install("python3_env", packages = c("whoosh", "jieba"))
use_virtualenv("python3_env", required = T)

whoosh <- reticulate::import("whoosh")

index <- whoosh$index$open_dir("legal_indexing", indexname = "document_index")

searcher <- index$searcher()

get_result <- possibly(
    \(x) {
        query <- whoosh$qparser$MultifieldParser(c("content", "title"), index$schema)$parse(x)

        return(result)
    },
    otherwise = "error!"
)
```
